<br>
As VI apparently intended, monks arent getting hit often, but when they do get hit it HURTS. With monks having so few hit points, Id imagine their main tanking days are fini, and their soloing days have been restricted as well...<br>
<br>
This may not be the case 50+, Im not sure. But in the mid levels it was a tough hit.<br>
<br>
Domenic Dominion<br>
&quot;Some say the world will end in fire...&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzeldagisravensoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zeldagis Ravensoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 2:38:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1571.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Monks</span><hr size=1> It really is about time this happened.  Pretty tough to be one of the two top damaging melee characters and be able to mitigate damage as one of the two top tanks also.  Monks, wearing leather, should always have been equivilent to rogues or just slightly above.<br>
<br>
Zel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarsissrazorscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarsiss Razorscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 2:53:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1571.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Monks</span><hr size=1> Thank you Zel for sharing your vision of what a monk should be. I really care. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukaisratahl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kais Ratahl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Clockwork Tiger<br>Lord of the Rawr<br> Mod of Maulings</span><br>  Posts: 596<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 2:56:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1571.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Monks</span><hr size=1> Been looking over the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508">Monky Business</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> forums. Not a happy place right now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzeldagisravensoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zeldagis Ravensoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 4:13:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1571.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   You cared enough to respond didn't you</span><hr size=1> Think about it.  How much sense did it make that Monks were among great damage dealers and good tanks?  Rogues are great damage dealers, bad tanks.  Rangers are great damage dealers, bad tanks.  Paladins -- shitty damage, good tank.  SK's --- see Paladin.  Warriors -- decent damage dealers, decent tanks (great tanks with right equip, hard to hold taunt without it though).<br>
<br>
Zel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1188<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 4:17:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1571.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Well, make sense or not ..</span><hr size=1> .. that was the game for 3 years.  It's never an issue before as far as who is the better tank until you consider a monk fully decked out with +100 HP items in all slots; ie. at the VERY high end.  Monks have pathetic HP -- worse than rogues.  They're on the priest table for HP. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarsissrazorscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarsiss Razorscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 4:21:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1571.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Well, make sense or not ..</span><hr size=1> Thank you Zel for sharing the reasoning behind your vision on what monks should be. I still really care. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ublakkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>blakkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 514<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/02 4:25:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1571.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: You cared enough to respond didn't you</span><hr size=1> Actually rogues are pretty good tanks, they have defence caps and defence skills  right up there with plate classes, and until this patch 32 more defense points than the other chain melee class (rangers).  They had to upgrade hybrids awhile back to move Rogues out of the number 3 tank slot.<br>
<br>
Personally I think monks were not unabalanced before, hmm let me correct myself.  Monks that weren't at the ac soft cap weren't unabalanced before.<br>
<br>
The imbalance came from mudflation, making alot of high end all/all or Monk/Plate wearable items with lots of AC and hitpoints.  The uber guild monks were then able to get near warrior hitpoints and mitigation (from ac at or above softcap) while maintaining their superior avoidance.<br>
<br>
So VI fixes the problem by lowering the mitigation table on monks by about 10 percent across the board.  Guess who this affects?  It affects mid level monks, and high end monks who are not at the ac softcap.  <br>
<br>
So.... Desired effect is to make High end guild, end game monks less tankable, the result was to leave them about the same (still have ac above softcap and high hitpoints from gear), while making it harder for non uber and lower level monks to survive day to day.<br>
<br>
